description.0: STARR RYDER and MARVEL BOY join forces to explore an ancient European tomb, only to bump into an unfriendly Army of the Undead!
description.2: Bob Grayson investigates potential cult activity that sees a number of insurance policies signed over to one man -- only for their owners to die shortly after. Featuring MARVEL BOY.
description.3: A massive planetoid is orbiting Earth and showering the planet with meteor fragments. Can Marvel Boy save Washington from...THE ZERO HOUR?
description.4: An alien from Uranus sends his son, who was born on Earth but fled from Nazis, back to his birthplace amongst humanity! A Uranian becomes an Earthling once again. Thus begins the tale of Marvel Boy!
description.17: Note: this issue only contains "Birth of Sub-Mariner" by Bill Everett. On panel for the first time! The incredible love story between Atlantis' Princess Fen and sailor Leonard McKenzie-Namor's parents!
description.22: "Terror at Sea."" Betty Dean's master novel about conman Harry Seller comes to life aboard a cruise ship!
description.26: "War-Cry of the Jungle!"" Sub-Mariner and Namora travel to Venezuela to find a group of missing American explorers, including Betty Dean.
description.27: Note: this issue only contains "Doom From the Sun" by Bill Everett. The malevolent Iron Brain is throwing off the Earth's atmosphere (and weather patterns) with his "Earth Mover" device. The ocean floor is heating up fast!
description.34: Note: this issue only contains "The Mystery of Pirate Cove!" by Bill Everett. Peppo LaRue is attempting to set up a new piratical crime base in Louisiana!
description.35: "The Last of the Vikings!"" A group of Viking descendants living in obscurity intend to declare war on the United States. Sub-Mariner and Namora try to talk them out of it.
description.40: Note: this issue only contains "A Case of King's Ransom" by Bill Everett. Snake Wilson, gambling crime lord, is Namor's latest opponent!
description.42: "Doomed in the Desert!"" After the descendent of a pharaoh unleashes an army of mummies on Cairo, Namora must find a way to kill the undead!
description.47: "The Lost City of Yucatan!"" Namora helps some explorers discover the lost Mayan city of Apaco. Chaos ensues.
description.50: Note: this issue only contains "The Case of the Frantic Fisherman" by Bill Everett. Namora springs into action against some no-good surface thugs… but a trap has already been laid.
description.54: "Case of the Disappearing Watchman!"" Sub-Mariner and Namora assist a young boy in finding his father, a former felon, who has gone missing.
description.55: Note: this issue only contains "Murder Motor Mart" by Bill Everett. A Sub-Mariner and Namora team-up!
description.56: "The Beast of the Bowery Barge!"" Sub-Mariner and Namora save a young girl from her cruel father.
description.59: "Case of the Deep Sea Swindle!"" Namora and her crew protect a trove of gold bullion on a ship headed to Central America.
description.61: "Blackbeard, Scourge of the Seas."" Sub-Mariner, Namora, and Betty Dean clash with Blackbeard and his cutthroat pirate crew.
description.64: Note: this issue only contains "The Harbor of Madmen" by Bill Everett. Atlantis' prince cooks up a half-baked plan… one that puts a surface girl in danger!
description.66: "Case of the Vanishing Venuses."" Sub-Mariner, Namora, and Betty Dean become extras in a movie directed by a deranged former starlet!
description.67: "Case of the Bends."" Sub-Mariner enlists Namora to help expose an evil doctor!
description.71: Note: this issue only contains "The Shark Strikes" by Bill Everett. The "Hammerhead" proves a wily foe… and as great a swimmer as Namor!
description.75: Note: this issue only contains "Mr. X--Master of Crime" by Bill Everett. Betty is at risk of becoming a shark's breakfast!
description.88: Note: this issue only contains "Sub-Mariner Vs. Green-Out" by Bill Everett. A classic caper starring Namor and Betty Dean!

6.text: The macho Man-God Apollo possesses hapless Marvin Klee! And now even Venus can’t resist his charm!

8.text: Venus embroils herself in a scheme to reunite two long lost lovers…and is met with some reluctance from Whitney Hammond!

10.text: Jupiter’s wrathful daughter Joya holds a trial for Venus condemning her love for a mortal man! Loki reveals his plot to destroy all Olympians!

13.text: Beauty Magazine does Mardi Gras...with Venus as their main attraction! But will the jealous Della Mason derail Beauty Mag’s float on the day of the parade? Guest-starring Loki in a pre-Marvel appearance!

18.text: Is this the end of Venus’ earth-bound days? The Goddess of Love’s presence is requested back on Olympus, although Jupiter offers up a challenge that would allow the goddess to remain on Earth with her beloved Whitney!

20.text: Venus can’t get over her feelings for Beauty Magazine Publisher Whitney Hammond, and decides to find a new boyfriend to make him jealous!

22.text: "Terror at Sea.” Betty Dean’s master novel about conman Harry Seller comes to life aboard a cruise ship!

26.text: "War-Cry of the Jungle!” Sub-Mariner and Namora travel to Venezuela to find a group of missing American explorers, including Betty Dean.

33.text: Venus helps the dejected Connie Lane resume her relationship with former high school sweetheart Rodney Radiant. But has the fame of celluloid stardom changed Radiant for good?

41.text: The Goddess of Love brings her street style to remote Cactus City...and this small town has never seen the likes of her beauty!

42.text: "Doomed in the Desert!” After the descendent of a pharaoh unleashes an army of mummies on Cairo, Namora must find a way to kill the undead!

47.text: "The Lost City of Yucatan!” Namora helps some explorers discover the lost Mayan city of Apaco. Chaos ensues.

48.text: The tale of Venus, a beautiful woman from another planet. But what purpose does a goddess-like alien have on earth? People flock to her beauty and surround her with grace, but what are Venus’ true intentions?

54.text: "Case of the Disappearing Watchman!” Sub-Mariner and Namora assist a young boy in finding his father, a former felon, who has gone missing.

56.text: "The Beast of the Bowery Barge!” Sub-Mariner and Namora save a young girl from her cruel father.

59.text: "Case of the Deep Sea Swindle!” Namora and her crew protect a trove of gold bullion on a ship headed to Central America.

61.text: "Blackbeard, Scourge of the Seas.” Sub-Mariner, Namora, and Betty Dean clash with Blackbeard and his cutthroat pirate crew.

67.text: "Case of the Bends.” Sub-Mariner enlists Namora to help expose an evil doctor!
